                            <comment id="421966" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 23 Jul 2024 12:45:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17367&quot; title=&quot;Failover on master: Invalid NID string&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17367&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17367&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should resolve this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="417397" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 11 Jun 2024 20:41:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I assume this is a mkfs_opts() issue in test-framework.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;opts+=&quot; --failnode=$(h2nettype ${!var})&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is h2nettype just returning $var?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="415618" author="adilger" created="Tue, 28 May 2024 20:19:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi James, could you please take a look at this.  It looks like fallout from the change to the NID parsing with &apos;&lt;tt&gt;:&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; separators in IPv6 NIDs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect the easiest fix would be to change the &lt;tt&gt;failover-part-&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt; test sessions to add &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#64;$NETTYPE&lt;/tt&gt; to the NIDs, but I haven&apos;t looked into the details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
